videos.description: Baylor's Juicy Landrum hits back-to-back 3's, while UConn's Crystal Dangerfield connects on a 3 of her own to open up the ballgame.
videos.headline: UConn, Baylor trade 3's to open game

videos.description: Baylor's NaLyssa Smith denies a layup with a powerful block underneath the rim.
videos.headline: Smith slaps it into crowd on block

videos.description: UConn's Katie Lou Samuelson lays it in before the buzzer sounds for the half and Baylor coach Kim Mulkey is not happy.
videos.headline: UConn's Samuelson scores before the halftime buzzer

videos.description: Chloe Jackson gets the steal on one end of the court then tosses it to Kalani Brown in the paint for the score, giving Baylor a convincing lead over UConn.
videos.headline: Baylor's Brown scores following steal

videos.description: Chloe Jackson grabs the ball after a block by UConn and hits an off-balance jumper to give Baylor a 63-55 lead in the final minutes of the game.
videos.headline: Baylor recovers after block on Jackson's jumper

videos.description: Baylor defeats UConn 68-57 for the Huskies' first regular season loss since November 2014.
videos.headline: No. 8 Baylor celebrates after beating No. 1 UConn

videos.description: Baylor coach Kim Mulkey compliments her players while holding her newborn grandson after the Lady Bears' upset over UConn.
videos.headline: Baylor coach Kim Mulkey celebrates with grandson after win

videos.description: Kalani Brown's double-double of 22 points and 17 rebounds propels Baylor to a 68-57 win vs. UConn, the Huskies' first regular-season loss in 126 games.
